			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I had a thread some time back about whether it was worth it to fully equip pets.  With the new insta-armor equipped ones, that side of it is a moot point now, but there's definately some good possibilities for weapons (mostly the proccing flavor) to equip the pet with.
<br />

<br />
Here's what I just bought and will be trying out tonight:
<br />

<br />
I'd love any feedback or additional suggestions.
<br />

<br />
Blood Point - piercing 10/21 +5 sta, +10 svd/svp effect : Siphon (steals 80 HP).
<br />
    With the summoned gear doing 150 dd, I figure if this procs as often, it ought to be worth it against most xp type mobs, where 80 health on your pet is worth at least another 80 to the enemy.  Cost about 450pp.
<br />

<br />
Bloodguard Wand of Walking Dead - 1hb 16/26 ac10 str/agi+9 hp+35 procs guard II  (how much does that absorb anyway?)
<br />
    Looks like it ought to be a good combo with the blood point.  Allows that 80 stolen hp to last longer, and do more damage in DS for the buck, plus the obvious advantage of just plain taking less damage.  Cost 140pp.
<br />

<br />
Melodious Truncheon - 1hb 11/23 effect melodious befuddlement - Befuddles your target with a soothing melody, causing them to fall unconscious and suffer from amnesia.
<br />
     If this does what it sounds like, I am hoping the pet will break off combat when it procs, and since mobs dont aggro on pets, maybe he can come back to me, regen, and then get sent back in again.  With focused pet regen, this might make a nice strategy.  No idea if it works like I am hoping though.  Cost 495pp.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyway, I'll be trying these out tonight and will post more feedback.
<br />

<br />
-Dretchulos
