			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Impressions on the ones I played around with tonight:
<br />

<br />
Bloodpoint - didn't proc very often.   WoX actually broke even against some caster mobs, but he comes close to doing that anyway more often than not.  Didn't think it was worth the cash.
<br />

<br />
Bloodguard Wand - worth it at 140pp.  Guard II didn't help as much as I had hoped, but it was noticeable most of the time.  Doesn't proc too often, but stays on long enough to keep it on the pet about 80% of the time if you keep him fighting constantly.  Maybe a good combo along with a slow proc for tanking planes xp.
<br />

<br />
Melodius Truncheon - Just a 1 tick mez like lucy says.  Mob is back on you before you can sneeze.  Not useful.
<br />

<br />
Sounds like a slow proc is the way to go in one hand, though I'm not convinced a snare is the best for the second.  Maybe a second slow proc just to make sure one gets off sooner.  Or some dd or guard.  Snare is good if you want to lead stuff around while pet heals, but I'm too impatient to do that a lot.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
